  "text": "Demographic entropy H is positively correlated with demographic stability, the capacity of a population to maintain steady state values of population numbers in spite of small variations in the individual birth and death rates [CITATION_1] . The main predictions of directionality theory derive from the analytical fact that entropy, and its correlate demographic stability, are the principal measures of selective outcome, and hence the main determinants of genotypic and phenotypic change under natural selection.",
